      "globalShareLabel": "~30% of global trade",
      "description": "The world's busiest and most economically vital waterway, the Strait of Malacca is at the heart of the Indo-Pacific economy. Each year, approximately 40% of global maritime trade flows through the narrow passage, with much of it stopping over at the Port of Singapore, the world's second-busiest port facility. With a width of approximately 2 miles at its narrowest and a depth of 82 feet at its shallowest, the strait has grown increasingly crowded over time, raising concerns about its future viability.",
