      "globalShareLabel": "~20% of global maritime trade",
      "description": "Stretching for approximately 230 miles from North to South, the Taiwan Strait forms the boundary between the People's Republic of China and the Republic of China (Taiwan). While the strait has long been a crucial artery for container ships bound for China, Japan and the Korean Peninsula, it has grown increasingly unsettled in recent decades as the PRC has escalated its military activity in the vicinity of Taiwan. Nevertheless, the waterway accounts for approximately 20% of global maritime trade by value.",
