      "globalShareLabel": "~12% of global trade by volume",
      "description": "A crucial gateway linking the Indian Ocean and the Red Sea (and thus the Suez Canal), the Bab el-Mandeb is among the world's foremost trade corridors. Due to its proximity to the oil-producing nations of the Middle East, the passage plays a key role in maritime petroleum supply chains, with large percentages of global oil exports flowing through it. However, regional conflicts have significantly threatened the stability of the strait, as Houthi militias based in Yemen have launched repeated attacks on commercial vessels.",
