      "description": "A key waterway separating Taiwan from the Philippines, the Luzon Strait serves as a crucial link in regional and transpacific trade networks. Large percentages of goods bound for the United States and other ports in the Americas transit the strait on a daily basis, while Japan relies heavily on the passage for energy imports. As tensions between the People's Republic of China and the Republic of China (Taiwan) have risen, the strait has also emerged as a key geopolitical faultline.",
