      "description": "The sole maritime connection between the Persian Gulf and the Indian Ocean, the Strait of Hormuz is a critical node in the global petroleum supply chain. For decades, huge volumes of Iranian oil have flowed through the narrow passage, with over 20 million barrels a day transiting in 2024, accounting for approximately 20% of global petroleum consumption. As tensions between Iran and the United States have mounted, however, the strait has become an increasingly contested space.",
